We use a dynamic programming approach to solve the problem. We create a 2D array (dp) with dimensions (n+1)x(m+1), where n is the length of s and m is the length of pattern. We iterate through the characters of s and pattern, comparing each character. If the characters match, we set dp[i][j] to j, indicating that the substring starting at index i in s and index j in pattern is a match. If the characters don't match, we take the minimum of dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1], which represents the minimum number of characters to change in s and pattern to make them match starting from indices i and j, respectively.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n.m) and space complexity of O(n.m), where n is the length of s and m is the length of pattern.

